{"id":"2BCfkBRHmbhytY8nm9spZ4inpFkqHBsLKs6LqzTxwmhuxSvfYzGLsd","title":"nixCraft: Linux Tips, Hacks, Tutorials, And Ideas In Blog Format (RSS/FEED)","displayTitle":"Dev - NixCraft","url":"https://www.cyberciti.com/atom/atom.xml","feedLink":"https://www.cyberciti.biz/atom/","items":[{"title":"zcommands: Read gzip Compressed Text Files On a Fly on Linux and Unix","url":"https://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/decompress-and-expand-text-files.html","date":1730493247,"author":"Vivek Gite","unread":true,"desc":"","content":"<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><p><img alt=\"zcommands Read gzip Compressed Text Files On a Fly on Linux and Unix\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-115476\" height=\"449\" src=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/wp-content/uploads/2007/08/zcommands-Read-gzip-Compressed-Text-Files-On-a-Fly-on-Linux-and-Unix.png\" width=\"599\"/><br/>\n<span class=\"drop_cap\">L</span>inux and Unix like operating systems comes with z* commands. These commands allow you to read gzip compressed text files using zless, zcat, zmore, and friends commands. The gzip command reduces the size of the files using Lempel-Ziv coding (LZ77).  Whenever possible, each file is replaced by one with the extension .gz while keeping the same ownership modes, access, and modification times. z* commands have some cool usage too, such as display the current time in different zonename.</p>\n<p>Love this? sudo share_on: <strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/decompress-and-expand-text-files.html&amp;text=zcommands: Read gzip Compressed Text Files On a Fly on Linux and Unix&amp;via=nixcraft\">Twitter</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/decompress-and-expand-text-files.html\">Facebook</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/decompress-and-expand-text-files.html\">LinkedIn</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://wa.me/?text=zcommands: Read gzip Compressed Text Files On a Fly on Linux and Unix https://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/decompress-and-expand-text-files.html\">Whatsapp</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://reddit.com/submit?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/decompress-and-expand-text-files.html&amp;title=zcommands: Read gzip Compressed Text Files On a Fly on Linux and Unix\">Reddit</a></strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/decompress-and-expand-text-files.html\">zcommands: Read gzip Compressed Text Files On a Fly on Linux and Unix</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/\">nixCraft</a>.</p></div>\n    ","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"How to install kvm-ok on Debian or Ubuntu Linux","url":"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/installing-kvm-ok-command-on-debian-ubuntu-linux/","date":1731740051,"author":"Vivek Gite","unread":true,"desc":"","content":"<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><div style=\"float: right; margin-top: 0; margin-left: 5px;\"><a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/category/linux-kvm/\" title=\"See all Linux Kernel Based Virtual Machine related FAQs/Howtos\"><img alt=\"See all Linux Kernel Based Virtual Machine related FAQs/Howtos\" border=\"0\" height=\"47\" src=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/media/new/category/old/kvm-logo.png\" width=\"150\"/></a></div>\n<p><span class=\"drop_cap\">T</span>he KVM-ok command command will tell you if your Debian or Ubuntu Linux-powered server can host hardware-accelerated KVM virtual machines. KVM (Kernel-based Virtual Machine) is a free and open-source virtualization technology that is used with every Linux kernel. In other words, KVM will make your Linux computer into a hypervisor, allowing you to run multiple isolated virtual machines (VMs) on a single physical machine. However, KVM depends upon CPU hardware virtualization extensions like Intel VT-x or AMD-V to provide high-performance virtual machines. This support must be enabled in the BIOS. Apart from that, some cloud service providers also allow nested virtualization that will help you to run VMs inside your instances. However, this may not be enabled in BIOS or instance configuration. Thus, you need to install the kvm-ok command to determine whether such support exists.</p>\n<p>Love this? sudo share_on: <strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/installing-kvm-ok-command-on-debian-ubuntu-linux/&amp;text=How to install kvm-ok on Debian or Ubuntu Linux&amp;via=nixcraft\">Twitter</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/installing-kvm-ok-command-on-debian-ubuntu-linux/\">Facebook</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/installing-kvm-ok-command-on-debian-ubuntu-linux/\">LinkedIn</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://wa.me/?text=How to install kvm-ok on Debian or Ubuntu Linux https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/installing-kvm-ok-command-on-debian-ubuntu-linux/\">Whatsapp</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://reddit.com/submit?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/installing-kvm-ok-command-on-debian-ubuntu-linux/&amp;title=How to install kvm-ok on Debian or Ubuntu Linux\">Reddit</a></strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/installing-kvm-ok-command-on-debian-ubuntu-linux/\">How to install kvm-ok on Debian or Ubuntu Linux</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/\" title=\"Linux and Unix tutorials for new and seasoned sysadmin section\">nixCraft</a>.</p></div>\n    ","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"How to find hard disk (SSD) serial numbers in Linux","url":"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/search-finding-hard-disk-ssd-serial-numbers-linux-command/","date":1731793115,"author":"Vivek Gite","unread":true,"desc":"","content":"<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><div style=\"float: right; margin-top: 0; margin-left: 5px;\"><a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/category/linux/\" title=\"See all GNU/Linux related FAQ\"><img alt=\"See all GNU/Linux related FAQ\" border=\"0\" height=\"128\" src=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/media/new/category/old/linux-logo.png\" width=\"128\"/></a></div>\n<p><span class=\"drop_cap\">Y</span>ou need to use the smartctl command to display the hard disk (SSD) serial numbers in Linux. This is useful when changing your hard disk if it goes bad. </p>\n<p>Love this? sudo share_on: <strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/search-finding-hard-disk-ssd-serial-numbers-linux-command/&amp;text=How to find hard disk (SSD) serial numbers in Linux&amp;via=nixcraft\">Twitter</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/search-finding-hard-disk-ssd-serial-numbers-linux-command/\">Facebook</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/search-finding-hard-disk-ssd-serial-numbers-linux-command/\">LinkedIn</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://wa.me/?text=How to find hard disk (SSD) serial numbers in Linux https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/search-finding-hard-disk-ssd-serial-numbers-linux-command/\">Whatsapp</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://reddit.com/submit?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/search-finding-hard-disk-ssd-serial-numbers-linux-command/&amp;title=How to find hard disk (SSD) serial numbers in Linux\">Reddit</a></strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/search-finding-hard-disk-ssd-serial-numbers-linux-command/\">How to find hard disk (SSD) serial numbers in Linux</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/\" title=\"Linux and Unix tutorials for new and seasoned sysadmin section\">nixCraft</a>.</p></div>\n    ","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"How to install vnstat on Debian 12/11 to monitor network interface bandwidth usage","url":"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/debian-linux-install-vnstat-console-network-traffic-monitor/","date":1732734422,"author":"Vivek Gite","unread":true,"desc":"","content":"<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><div style=\"float: right; margin-top: 0; margin-left: 5px;\"><a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/category/debian-ubuntu/\" title=\"See all Debian/Ubuntu Linux related FAQ\"><img alt=\"See all Debian/Ubuntu Linux related FAQ\" border=\"0\" height=\"63\" src=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/media/new/category/old/debianlogo.gif\" width=\"54\"/></a></div>\n<p><span class=\"drop_cap\">D</span>o you need to keep track of the network traffic (bandwidth) usage for the Network interface controller (NIC) of your Debian Linux-based cloud or bare metal server? Look no forward. Try the vnStat, a free and open-source console-based network traffic monitor that keeps a log of 5-minute intervals, hourly, daily, monthly, and yearly network traffic for the selected interface. Once installed, vnStat can be used even without root permissions on most systems.</p>\n<p>Love this? sudo share_on: <strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/debian-linux-install-vnstat-console-network-traffic-monitor/&amp;text=How to install vnstat on Debian 12/11 to monitor network interface bandwidth usage&amp;via=nixcraft\">Twitter</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/debian-linux-install-vnstat-console-network-traffic-monitor/\">Facebook</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/debian-linux-install-vnstat-console-network-traffic-monitor/\">LinkedIn</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://wa.me/?text=How to install vnstat on Debian 12/11 to monitor network interface bandwidth usage https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/debian-linux-install-vnstat-console-network-traffic-monitor/\">Whatsapp</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://reddit.com/submit?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/debian-linux-install-vnstat-console-network-traffic-monitor/&amp;title=How to install vnstat on Debian 12/11 to monitor network interface bandwidth usage\">Reddit</a></strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/debian-linux-install-vnstat-console-network-traffic-monitor/\">How to install vnstat on Debian 12/11 to monitor network interface bandwidth usage</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/\" title=\"Linux and Unix tutorials for new and seasoned sysadmin section\">nixCraft</a>.</p></div>\n    ","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"https://www.cyberciti.biz/media/new/faq/2024/11/vnstat-demo.webm","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"How to enable mouse to copy & paste in vim","url":"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/enable-vim-mouse-copy-paste-in-ubuntu-debian-linux-unix/","date":1732801475,"author":"Vivek Gite","unread":true,"desc":"","content":"<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><div style=\"float: right; margin-top: 0; margin-left: 5px;\"><a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/category/vim/\" title=\"See all VI / Vim text editor related FAQs/HowTos\"><img alt=\"See all VI / Vim text editor related FAQs/HowTos\" border=\"0\" height=\"60\" src=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/media/new/category/old/vim-logo.png\" width=\"61\"/></a></div>\n<p><span class=\"drop_cap\">S</span>ome Linux distro like Debian or specific BSD variants provide very little configuration support for mouse out of the box for Vim. Let us see how to paste in Vim using a mouse by enabling support, which is useful for new developers and sysadmin coming from Windows background.</p>\n<p>Love this? sudo share_on: <strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/enable-vim-mouse-copy-paste-in-ubuntu-debian-linux-unix/&amp;text=How to enable mouse to copy &amp; paste in vim&amp;via=nixcraft\">Twitter</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/enable-vim-mouse-copy-paste-in-ubuntu-debian-linux-unix/\">Facebook</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/enable-vim-mouse-copy-paste-in-ubuntu-debian-linux-unix/\">LinkedIn</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://wa.me/?text=How to enable mouse to copy &amp; paste in vim https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/enable-vim-mouse-copy-paste-in-ubuntu-debian-linux-unix/\">Whatsapp</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://reddit.com/submit?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/enable-vim-mouse-copy-paste-in-ubuntu-debian-linux-unix/&amp;title=How to enable mouse to copy &amp; paste in vim\">Reddit</a></strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/enable-vim-mouse-copy-paste-in-ubuntu-debian-linux-unix/\">How to enable mouse to copy &amp; paste in vim</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/\" title=\"Linux and Unix tutorials for new and seasoned sysadmin section\">nixCraft</a>.</p></div>\n    ","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"MySQL Change root Password Command","url":"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/mysql-change-root-password/","date":1733761140,"author":"Vivek Gite","unread":true,"desc":"","content":"<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><div style=\"float: right; margin-top: 0; margin-left: 5px;\"><a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/category/mysql/\" title=\"See all MySQL Database Server related FAQ\"><img alt=\"See all MySQL Database Server related FAQ\" border=\"0\" height=\"52\" src=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/media/new/category/old/mysqllogo.gif\" width=\"100\"/></a></div>\n<p><span class=\"drop_cap\">H</span>ow do I change MySQL root password under Linux, FreeBSD, OpenBSD and UNIX-like like operating system over the ssh session?</p>\n<p>Love this? sudo share_on: <strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/mysql-change-root-password/&amp;text=MySQL Change root Password Command&amp;via=nixcraft\">Twitter</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/mysql-change-root-password/\">Facebook</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/mysql-change-root-password/\">LinkedIn</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://wa.me/?text=MySQL Change root Password Command https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/mysql-change-root-password/\">Whatsapp</a></strong> - <strong><a href=\"https://reddit.com/submit?url=https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/mysql-change-root-password/&amp;title=MySQL Change root Password Command\">Reddit</a></strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/mysql-change-root-password/\">MySQL Change root Password Command</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/\" title=\"Linux and Unix tutorials for new and seasoned sysadmin section\">nixCraft</a>.</p></div>\n    ","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""}]}